== Noun ==

holmberry
  1. a holly bush. Used as an adjective in Thomas Hardy's "Tess of the d'Urbervilles." "Let me put one little kiss on those holmberry lips, Tess, or even on that warmed cheek, and I'll stop - on my honour, I will!"
Could be a derivative of "holm tree" - evergreen oak of southern Europe having leaves somewhat resembling those of holly